&lt;p&gt;Please note qualification from PWP (IAPT)Training Course or equivalent i.e. Qualified Graduate Mental Health Worker with significant and relevant Primary Care experience is essential to this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Service/Ward/Department Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Stockport Healthy Minds is part of the Improving Access to Psychological Therapies (IAPT) Programme and offers assessment and treatment for people referred via their GP or through a self referral pathway, with common mental health problems. The service works with adults aged 16 and above, from various backgrounds. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The service is made up of a multidisciplinary team, including Psychological Wellbeing Practitioners, Counsellors, Cognitive Behavioural Therapists, EMDR therapists and Psychotherapists.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Stockport Healthy Minds are looking to recruit an enthusiastic and committed qualified PWP to join their highly successful and motivated team. For the role, you must have a Diploma/Certificate in Low Intensity Psychological interventions in order to provide high volume, low intensity CBT interventions for people with common mental health problems. Assessments and interventions will mainly be delivered online via CCBT platforms, telephone or via video link for both individual and group interventions. The successful candidate will have excellent written and spoken communication skills along with the ability to work flexibly, including the flexibility of working remotely where necessary. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Please see Job Description and Person Specification for further details&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name:Kim Wright&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Step 2 Team Manager&lt;/p&gt;
